{"title":"With immigration, perceptions matter more than reality","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/900214955/0/marginalrevolution~With-immigration-perceptions-matter-more-than-reality.html","date":1719549939000,"content":"<p>That is the topic of <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2024-06-25/immigration-perceptions-matter-more-than-reality-in-us-or-sweden?utm_source=twitter&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=socialflow-organic&amp;cmpid%3D=socialflow-twitter-view&amp;utm_content=view&amp;sref=htOHjx5Y&amp;embedded-checkout=true\" target=\"_blank\">my latest Bloomberg column</a>.  Rather than work through the argument, which requires you to read the whole column, I’ll just reproduce the most trollish part:</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>When I am in a foreign city and in search of interesting food, I have a trick: In which neighborhood, I ask the locals, am I most likely to get murdered? In Stockholm, Rinkeby was the answer, even though many of the people I asked had never been.</p>\r\n<p>So I went to <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rinkeby\" target=\"_blank\">Rinkeby</a>, which is mostly non-White and most notably Somalian. There were Yemeni, Ethiopian, Persian and other restaurants. (I had a good chicken mandi at one called <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.facebook.com/p/Maida-Restaurant-100063792685063/?locale=sv_SE\" target=\"_blank\">Maida</a>.) I felt safe the entire time, and saw plenty of solo women, including some blonde Swedes, walking leisurely along the main street, as well as many women with head coverings. I saw a Western Union office and a driving school, signs that people have some funds to send away or invest in a car.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>I hope to write a longer post on immigration for you all soon.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/06/with-immigration-perceptions-matter-more-than-reality.html\">With immigration, perceptions matter more than reality</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/900214955/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/900214955/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/900214955/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/900214955/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/x.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/19/900214955/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/email20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/20/900214955/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/rss20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/06/with-immigration-perceptions-matter-more-than-reality.html#comments\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/comments20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/06/with-immigration-perceptions-matter-more-than-reality.html/feed\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/commentsrss20.png\" /></a> \r\n<div><a href=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/06/with-immigration-perceptions-matter-more-than-reality.html#comments\"><h3>Comments</h3></a><ul><li><a href=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/06/with-immigration-perceptions-matter-more-than-reality.html#comment-160774376\">In reply to Phil S..   “ a